{
  "title": "HASEonGPU",
  "description": "HASEonGPU is open-source HPC software for calculating amplified spontaneous emission (ASE) flux in laser gain media. It supports the design and analysis of high-power laser systems by estimating ASE flux for gain-medium geometry, pumping configuration, and material setup. Release 2.0 ships the Python frontend and compiled C++ backend as one supported release unit, using adaptive Monte Carlo ray tracing with GPU acceleration and distributed execution.",
